alert.note: Alert for Dixie; Taylor (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued June 25 at 9:13PM EDT until further notice by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida... Steinhatchee River near Steinhatchee (US 19) affecting Dixie and Taylor Counties. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Steinhatchee River near Steinhatchee (US 19). * WHEN...Until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 19.5 feet, Water begins to flood downstream at Steinhatchee Falls Park. Minor flooding of roads begins along River Road NE. Water will begin to encroach onto the yards of residences in the Ancient Oaks Community in Steinhatchee. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:45 PM EDT Sunday the stage was 21.2 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 8:45 PM EDT Sunday was 21.5 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 19.5 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 21.2 feet on 03/03/1966. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Monday afternoon at 315 PM EDT.
